# Official-source record

The market rule states: "The primary resolution sources for this market will be official information from Iranian aviation authorities and a consensus of credible reporting."

No merits official-source packet has been built before the open-record run. The attorneys should search for and submit official Iranian aviation authority records, notices to airmen / NOTAM material where publicly available, airport authority records, flight tracking records used only with appropriate caution, and credible reporting.

The market rule itself cites these examples, preserved in source-captures/polymarket-gamma-event.json:

- Reuters, January 2026 total closure example: https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/iran-shuts-airspace-most-flights-flightradar24-says-2026-01-14/
- Reuters, April 2024 western airspace closure example: https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/iranian-airports-cancel-flights-until-monday-morning-2024-04-14/
- Anadolu, January 27, 2026 non-qualifying partial Strait of Hormuz notice example: https://www.aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iran-issues-airspace-notice-for-military-drills-near-strait-of-hormuz/3812508
- bne IntelliNews, January 25-April 25, 2026 non-qualifying VFR suspension example: https://www.intellinews.com/iran-suspends-general-aviation-and-vfr-flights-in-new-airspace-directive-421997/
